Current Code Analysis
In your current code:

    -Main thread uses Thread.sleep(300)
    -Worker threads (Worker-1, Worker-2, Worker-3) don't have any sleep
What Happens Internally
    1.Main Thread Execution:
        -Main thread starts and creates worker threads
        -When it hits Thread.sleep(300), it goes to TIMED_WAITING state
        -This allows other threads to run
    2.Worker Threads Execution:
        -Worker threads run their loops without any sleep()
        -However, they don't run to completion in one go due to:
            -> Time Slicing: The OS allocates time slices to each thread
            -> Preemptive Multitasking: The OS can interrupt a running thread to give others a chance
            -> Thread Yielding: The JVM/OS may decide to switch threads even without sleep()
Why Thread Switching Happens Without sleep()
    -Even without sleep(), thread switching occurs because:

1.Time Slicing:
    -Modern OSes use preemptive scheduling
    -Each thread gets a small time quantum (typically 10-100ms)
    -After this time, the OS may switch to another thread
2.System Calls:
    -Operations like System.out.println() are I/O operations
    -These can cause thread context switches
3.JVM/OS Decisions:
    -The JVM or OS may decide to switch threads for:
        -> Fairness (giving all threads a chance to run)
        -> System load balancing
        -> Other system events
